.TH "drbd_bm_mark_for_writeout" 9 "drbd_bm_mark_for_writeout" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drbd_bm_mark_for_writeout \- mark a page with a "hint" to be considered for writeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drbd_bm_mark_for_writeout
.BI "(struct drbd_device *device "  ","
.BI "int page_nr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
DRBD device.
.IP "page_nr" 12
the bitmap page to mark with the "hint" flag
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
From within an activity log transaction, we mark a few pages with these
hints, then call \fBdrbd_bm_write_hinted\fP, which will only write out changed
pages which are flagged with this mark.
